WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.180
So I'm tasked with talking about liquid biopsies, not for genotyping or MRD, but as expression

00:00:09.180 --> 00:00:10.720
profiling platforms.

00:00:11.440 --> 00:00:14.880
Just as a matter of business, these are my disclosures.

00:00:16.100 --> 00:00:21.840
So when we talk about liquid biopsies, we can talk about a lot of different molecules,

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:29.120
but some of the molecules of interest are DNA and RNA molecules that are shed from normal

00:00:29.120 --> 00:00:35.300
and malignant tissues into the circulation, and that can give us a non-invasive window

00:00:35.300 --> 00:00:38.240
into both health and disease.

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:50.300
From a tube of blood, the plasma compartment can be studied to find DNA aberrations in

00:00:50.960 --> 00:00:58.980
genomic lesions, epigenetic landscape, some emerging methods.

00:00:59.120 --> 00:01:04.780
I'll talk about fragmentomic features, and then finally, gene expression, inferred and

00:01:04.780 --> 00:01:06.940
direct, and we'll be talking about that aspect.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:14.640
So what's been done so far, these are two kind of canvassing landscape-type papers.

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:20.560
The first is a paper in Nature from a group in Israel using whole genome bisulfite sequencing

00:01:20.560 --> 00:01:26.380
and looking at cell-free nucleic acids to see what the composition is, but it's not

00:01:26.380 --> 00:01:29.000
so important to look at the pie chart and figure out.

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:33.300
It's important to look at what the exact proportions are, but simply getting an idea

00:01:33.300 --> 00:01:38.360
that liquid biopsies can give us a window into many different cell types, including

00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:40.240
non-hematopoietic ones.

00:01:40.240 --> 00:01:45.600
On the right is another study from Stanford, from Steve Quake's group, looking at cell-free

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:48.280
RNA and whole transcriptome profiling.

00:01:48.280 --> 00:01:58.240
Again, the pie has many slices that aggregate the experience of tissue homeostasis from

00:01:58.240 --> 00:02:00.720
many different organs.

00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:03.760
So what's been done with these kinds of technologies?

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:07.920
One thing that you may have heard about is the idea of multi-cancer early detection,

00:02:07.920 --> 00:02:11.580
a drop of blood in tests for many cancer types.

00:02:11.580 --> 00:02:13.680
